  "prompt": "What are the new features in iPhone 7?",
  "response": "The iPhone 7 was released in September 2016, and it introduced several new features and improvements over its predecessor, the iPhone 6s. Some of the key new features of the iPhone 7 include:\n\n1. Water and dust resistance: The iPhone 7 was the first iPhone to have an IP67 rating, meaning it can withstand being submerged in up to 1 meter of water for up to 30 minutes.\n\n2. Improved camera: The iPhone 7 has a 12-megapixel rear-facing camera with optical image stabilization, a wider f/1.8 aperture, and a six-element lens. It also has a quad-LED True Tone flash for better low-light performance.\n\n3. New home button: The iPhone 7 has a new solid-state home button that uses haptic feedback to simulate the feel of a physical button press.\n\n4. Stereo speakers: The iPhone 7 has stereo speakers, with one speaker at the bottom of the phone and the other in the earpiece. This results in improved audio quality and louder volume.\n\n5. A10 Fusion chip: The iPhone 7 is powered by the A10 Fusion chip, which is a more powerful and energy-efficient processor than the A9 chip in the iPhone 6s.\n\n6. No headphone jack: The iPhone 7 was the first iPhone to not have a traditional 3.5mm headphone jack. Instead, it comes with a pair of Lightning-enabled EarPods and a Lightning-to-3.5mm adapter.\n\n7. New colors: The iPhone 7 was available in five colors: Jet Black, Black, Silver, Gold, and Rose Gold. The Jet Black color was a new glossy finish that was exclusive to the iPhone 7.",
